Frogule

About:

Frogules are native inhabitants of the Cordisec realm, known for their soft, squishy, and amorphous bodies that vaguely resemble frogs. Their appearance is marked by:

  • Bulbous, gelatinous forms
  • Moist skin
  • nub limbs and large, expressive eyes

Behaviour:

  • Wobbling around in tight clusters
  • Clinging to damp surfaces or nestled in mossy crevices
  • Making gentle gurgling or chirping noises

Despite their harmless look, Frogules play a vital role in the Cordisec realm's biological balance by feeding on decaying material

Uses:

Some alchemists collect Frogules for their Mucus, which has mild hallucinogenic effects

They are a beloved and peculiar part of the Cordisec's organic-magical ecosystem and often collected to as pets.
